What will be the output of the following code?
```javascript
console.log(a);
var a = 10;

console.log(b);
let b = 20;
```

What is the output of this code?
```javascript
const obj = Object.freeze({ user: { age: 25 } });
obj.user.age = 30;
console.log(obj.user.age);
```

What is the difference between passing `null` vs `undefined` as a function argument if there is a default parameter?
```javascript
function greet(name = 'Guest') { console.log(name); }
greet(undefined);
greet(null);
```

What will be printed to the console?
```javascript
function createCounter() {
  let count = 0;
  return () => ++count;
}
const c1 = createCounter();
const c2 = createCounter();
c1(); c1();
console.log(c2());
```

What is the output of the following code?
```javascript
const user = {
  name: 'Dave',
  greet: function() {
    console.log(this.name);
  }
};
const func = user.greet;
func();
```

Can you call a function expression before it is declared in the code?
```javascript
myFunc();
var myFunc = function() { console.log('Hello'); };
```

What will be the output?
```javascript
const arr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
const res = arr.filter(n => n > 2).map(n => n * 2);
console.log(res);
```

What is the output of this object destructuring?
```javascript
const user = { name: 'Alice' };
const { name, age = 25 } = user;
console.log(age);
```

What is the correct output order?
```javascript
console.log('1');
setTimeout(() => console.log('2'), 0);
Promise.resolve().then(() => console.log('3'));
console.log('4');
```
